 off the /proc files, and if it turns out you don't <br />have anything that uses it, you can avoid the warning by actually having a <br />smaller kernel with less crap, rather than adding more crap to hide the <br />crap. Wouldn't that be nicer?<br /><br />It would have to be a Kconfig option since we don't _know_ that it's not <br />used by anything..<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
